snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a capitalist.

I believe people who build Companies to a certain scale should have the option to pay $0 taxes if that tax amount is reinvested into their business to improve efficiency, infrastructure, people, etc... not dividends to shareholders.

The tax base grows proportionately to investment back within the business that makes it more competitive on a Global scale and the average working woman/man is rewarded for efforts put in.

Making a profit and doing right by the people who put in the work should be in divisible.

I'm a social liberal and financial conservative- we need leadership that meets in the middle and provides solutions for all.

We need a rebalancing of our priorities. The entrepreneur and innovator's should be celebrated and reap the rewards of their efforts. The average working person should be able to afford a life void of financial insecurity- what they do with their income is their responsibility.

When the vast majority of the populace is 1 pay cheque away from financial ruin- we have a problem.

snippet.textDisplay: The word socialism has been unfairly demonized quite effectively by the far right, including Republicans  & establishment Democrats. & the ability to explain, educate, & undo the damage done to the term socialism is in many cases, for some segments of the population, insurmountable. Propaganda works, Goebbels (Nazi Propaganda Minister)argued that the bigger the lie, the more likely the average person will believe it. Facts: among the advanced, industrialized democracies in the world, a huge portion of their economies are socialist. Any publicly financed program is a socialist program--government, military, public schools, infrastructure creation & maintenance, fire & police depts., libraries, even the internet was the creation of research & development by the government (military). & government plays the critical role of regulating capitalism & taxing society. A purely capitalist system without socialist programs & institutions would destroy itself because the most powerful financial institutions would completely marginalize the working people to such an extent that the majority would not have the basic income to spend on the goods & services being produced, resulting in the rise of an authoritarian state. Democracy, & its very survival is dependent on a strong, stable middle class with the purchasing power to maintain a sizeable free market. What Republicans have been able to do is hijack religious institutions & its leaders to promote support for the far right using abortion, school prayer, & guns to get the working people to essentially cut their own economic throats when they vote Republican. Establishment Democrats have been just as bad in some cases as Republicans. To effectively argue & debate the positive need for socialist institutions is extraordinarily difficult because it is complex. An effective political leader has to carefully navigate & explain the importance of socialism while they are being vilified, which is what is happening to Bernie Sanders. Joe Biden is a lapdog for Republicans & the far right, willing to compromise to the detriment of working people. Look what he did to Anita Hill  when he was the chair of the Judiciary Committee, not allowing women who had been sexually harassed by Clarence Thomas to speak before the committee. But if Bernie doesn't get selected, I would still vote for the Democratic party's nominee. It's a binary choice in a "winner-take-all" in the U.S. political system. 3rd parties serve to be spoilers, so one has to choose between the lesser of the 2 evils & Trump is a serious threat to the survival of democracy. I wish I had an inside voice to participate in educating & better informing leaders of the Democratic progressive wing. As a retired college professor I believe that I have a lot to share.
